%description:
The Mobile Access Gateway registers the mobile node with a Proxy Binding Update. [Required -- RFC 5213 6.9.1]

In Proxy Mobile IPv6 the network, not the host, manages mobility: when a mobile node attaches, its
serving Mobile Access Gateway (MAG) registers it with the Local Mobility Anchor (LMA) by sending a
Proxy Binding Update -- a Binding Update with the Proxy-Registration (P) flag set -- over the
backhaul, on the node's behalf. The mobile node itself runs no mobility software. Observed on the
wire at mag1's backhaul interface as it transmits the Proxy Binding Update.

%file: Pmipv6_ProxyBindingUpdate.cc

#include "ProtocolTest.h"

namespace inet {
namespace protocoltest {

Define_ProtocolTest(ipv6_pmipv6_proxy_binding_update)
{
    return ProtocolTest("ipv6_pmipv6_proxy_binding_update")
        .once(on("mag1.eth[0].mac").signal("packetSentToLower")
                  .packet("BindingUpdate.proxyRegistrationFlag == true")
                  .describe("mag1's Proxy Binding Update to the LMA").within(8));
}

} // namespace protocoltest
} // namespace inet

%inifile: test.ini

[General]
*.tester.testName = "ipv6_pmipv6_proxy_binding_update"
include ../../ini/_pmipv6.ini

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST ipv6_pmipv6_proxy_binding_update: PASS
